@edsantiago PTAL

I don't want to close issue #9597 with this PR since the underlying root cause remains unclear.  The good news is that the issue is easy to reproduce on my workstation with:

> ./bin/podman-remote run --replace --name test alpine sh -c 'start=0; if test -s log; then start=`tail -n 1 log`; fi; seq `expr $start + 1` `expr $start + 10` | tee -a log'; ./bin/podman-remote start -a test
